{"type":"text","timestamp":1775845315739,"sessionID":"ses_28762fd77ffe2wOKfgwZXpcMby","part":{"id":"prt_d78a0d428001h3ySfRu28XWea4","messageID":"msg_d78a0c03d001j9QJrF5QlhXLhy","sessionID":"ses_28762fd77ffe2wOKfgwZXpcMby","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the verification report.\n\n---\n\n## AR-017 Verification Report: PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n### Quality Gates\n\n| Check | Status |\n|-------|--------|\n| `go build ./pkg/picod/...` | ✅ PASS |\n| `go test ./pkg/picod/...` | ✅ PASS (all 39 tests) |\n| `go test -race ./pkg/picod/...` | ✅ PASS (no races) |\n| `go vet ./pkg/picod/...` | ✅ PASS (clean) |\n| No `log.Printf` usage | ✅ PASS |\n\n### Spec Requirement Verification\n\n| Requirement | Status | Details |\n|-------------|--------|---------|\n| **AuthManager struct** (`publicKey` + `mutex`) | ✅ PASS | `auth.go:19-22` matches spec exactly |\n| **LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()** | ✅ PASS | `auth.go:24-50` — reads env, PEM decode, PKIX parse, RSA verify, write lock |\n| **AuthMiddleware()** JWT validation | ✅ PASS | `auth.go:52-101` — Bearer extract, RS256 verify, exp/iat required, 1min leeway, MaxBytesReader |\n| **Constants** (`PublicKeyEnvVar`, `MaxBodySize`) | ✅ PASS | `types.go:7-8` — values match spec |\n| **Server integration** (`authManager` field, init, routes) | ✅ PASS | `server.go:14-70` — NewServer loads key+checkFatal, registerRoutes applies middleware to `/api`, `/health` public |\n| **Error response format** (JSON 401) | ✅ PASS | `auth.go:56-95` — consistent `{error, code, detail}` format |\n| **Middleware order** (Logger→Recovery→Auth→Handler) | ✅ PASS | `server.go:25,62` |\n| **Thread safety** (RWMutex) | ✅ PASS | `auth.go:45-47` (write lock), `auth.go:80-82` (read lock) |\n\n### ❌ Missing Tests (per tasks.md T4-T6)\n\n| Missing Test | Task | Spec Scenario |\n|-------------|------|---------------|\n| `TestAuthMiddleware_ClockLeeway` | T5.1 | Clock leeway tolerates minor skew (exp 30s ago → accepted) |\n| `TestAuthManager_ConcurrentReads` | T6.1 | Concurrent reads do not block |\n| `TestAuthManager_ConcurrentReadWrite` | T6.2 | Key update is thread-safe (race detector) |\n| `TestServer_ApiRoutesAcceptValidJWT` | T4.6 | `/api` routes accept valid JWT (200) |\n\n### 🐛 Bug: NonRSAKey Test Does Not Test What It Claims\n\n`TestAuthManager_LoadPublicKeyFromEnv_NonRSAKey` (`auth_test.go:76-94`) generates an **RSA** key (not EC), sets it as env, and asserts `require.NoError`. This test **passes** but does not verify non-RSA rejection. The spec requires: GIVEN a non-RSA key (e.g., EC), THEN `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` returns error containing \"public key is not RSA\".\n\n### Summary\n\n| Category | Result |\n|----------|--------|\n| Implementation correctness | ✅ Matches spec |\n| API contracts | ✅ All match |\n| Core tests | ✅ 9/9 auth tests pass |\n| Missing tests | ❌ 4 tests not implemented (T4.6, T5, T6.1, T6.2) |\n| Buggy test | ❌ `TestAuthManager_LoadPublicKeyFromEnv_NonRSAKey` uses wrong key type |\n| Code quality gates | ✅ All pass |\n\n**Verdict:** Implementation is correct and matches the spec, but test coverage is incomplete — 4 tests from tasks.md T4-T6 are missing, and 1 existing test (`NonRSAKey`) has a logic bug that makes it a false positive.","time":{"start":1775845315736,"end":1775845315736}}}
